{
  "doc_id": "35798",
  "text": "A variety of different approaches to predict drug metabolism have been described: rule-, ligand-protein-, and ligand-based methods [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Other approaches include ab initio, classic pharmacophore, and three-dimensional quantitative structure-activity relationship pharmacophore-based methods [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] ). Unfortunately, obstacles such as biological factors and substrate-product selectivity still hinder the widespread use of drug metabolism as a reliable tool [CITATION_6] .",
